	abstract = {Hydrous silicate melts appear to have greater compressibility relative to anhydrous melts of the same composition at low pressures ({\textless}2 GPa); however, at higher pressures, this difference is greatly reduced and becomes very small at pressures above 5 GPa. This implies that the pressure effect on the partial molar volume of water in silicate melt
              
                
              
