142Nd/144Nd ratios between chondrites and
terrestrial rocks can be explained by fractional crystallization with a decay timescale of the order of 1Gyr. These combined constraints yield thermal evolution models in which radiogenic heat production and latent heat exchange prevent early cooling of the core and possibly delay the onset of the geodynamo to 3.4-4Gyr ago.},
	urldate = {2020-05-02},
	journal = {Nature},
	author = {Labrosse, S. and Hernlund, J. W. and Coltice, N.},
	month = dec,
	year = {2007},
